"Abstract In the first two articles of this series, we saw how the Internet has enabled E-criminals to take advantage of the technology it offers to commit crimes against businesses on a global basis. Individuals who use the Internet to buy goods or use services are similarly exposed. In the following two articles we will look at the E-crimes which are being committed principally against individuals, although in the first topic, credit card fraud, it is usually businesses, or their insurers, that will pick up the tab."
